claim.claim-text:
18. A process for restoring color of a faded color negative, the process comprising the steps of: 
taking a faded color negative, and creating a blue enhancement mask of the faded negative; 
taking the faded color negative and passing yellow biased light though the faded color negative onto intermediate film stock to generate unprocessed intermediate stock; 
packing the blue enhancement mask with the unprocessed intermediate stock and passing blue light through the blue enhancement mask to creates an improved intermediate stock.
